<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="m" from="-0.75" to="0.75" step="0.25" exclude="0"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="b" from="-3" to="3" step="1" exclude="0"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="c" from="-1" to="1" step="0.5" exclude="0 $h"/>
  <number name="cplus">$c+$m/(2*$b)</number>
   
  <function name="L" symbolic="false" >
    $m*x + $b
  </function>
  
  <function name="f" symbolic="false" >
    $a*(x-$h)^2-$k
  </function>

</setup>


<p>A certain function <m>y=p(x)</m> has its localization at 
  <m>a = $c</m> given by <m>L(x)= $L</m>.
</p>

<p>
    <ol marker="a.">
      <li>
        <p>
          Determine the values of <m>p($c)</m> and <m>p'($c)</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>p($c)=</m><answer><award>$$L($c)</award></answer>
        </p>  
        <p>
          <m>p'($c)=</m><answer><award>$m</award></answer>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Estimate the value of <m>p($cplus)</m>.
        </p> 
        <p>
          <m>p($cplus) \approx </m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.1" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$L($cplus)</award></answer>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Suppose that <m>p''($c)=0</m> and you know that <m>p''($c) < 0</m> for <m>x < $c</m> and <m>p''($c) > 0</m> for <m>x > $c</m>. 
        </p>
        <p>
          From all the given information, it follows that our estimate of <m>p($cplus)</m> in part (b) is       
        <answer>
          <choiceInput name="overunder" inline>
            <choice>greater than</choice>
            <choice>less than</choice>
            <choice>equal to</choice>
          </choiceInput>            
            <award>
              <when>$overunder.selectedIndices=1 and $cplus < $c   
              </when>
            </award>  
            <award>
              <when>$overunder.selectedIndices=2 and $cplus > $c 
              </when> 
            </award>
          </answer> 
          the true value of <m>p($cplus)</m>, since <m>p''($c)</m> is 
          <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason1" inline>
              <choice>positive</choice>
              <choice>zero</choice>
              <choice>negative</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=1 and $cplus > $c       
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=3 and $cplus < $c 
                </when>
              </award>
          </answer>, so near <m>x = $c</m>, <m>f</m> is
          <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason2" inline>
              <choice>concave up</choice>
              <choice>linear</choice>
              <choice>concave down</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=1 and $cplus > $c     
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason2.selectedIndices=3 and $cplus < $c  
                </when>
              </award>
          </answer>, which makes the tangent line to <m>f</m> at the point <m>($c,p($c))</m> lie
     <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason3" inline>
              <choice>below</choice>
              <choice>above</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason3.selectedIndices=2 and $cplus < $c   
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason3.selectedIndices=1 and $cplus > $c  
                </when> 
              </award>
      </answer>   
    the curve.
        </p>
      </li>

    </ol>
</p>